<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99724100853618>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>OK, here goes</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Aug 7th 11:23 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73890><span id= >Segfreid</span></a><br><span id=notbold>28 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Gonna dump all the info i have about playing a wiz (got mine to 32 before switching servers)&nbsp;&nbsp;first off, look up your spells online before buying them, make sure it's something you will put to use, dont waste the plat otherwise.  Most important spells are the DD, the shield spells (minor, major, etc...) root, and snare (at 24, and careful, it's AoE, so you can snare yourself if you are to close to your target)<br><br>Yes, wiz can out-damage the other clases, but it's important to be aware that doing so will make the monster charge you, which is bad with your low hp.  Be sure to learn the balance point where you do the most damage without getting it more mad at you than at the tanks.<br><br>As far as the wizard damage shield (DS) goes, it's not worth buying, magicians and druids both have better, let them take care of that.  Be sure to also learn to balance how much mana you burn on a per kill basis, dont waste all your mana on one or two kills and then have to sit out for another two or three cause you dont have mana.<br><br>As far as soloing goes, dont bother with melee after 15 or so, it will be a waste of time better spent meditating, you dont do enough damage to warant trying to poke holes in the mob, better to nuke and med instead of wasting all that med time trying to stab something to death that you could have blasted once to kill<br><br>Well.... enought of my blathering, Hope some of this helps out, and good luck</p>&nbsp;<br>Cry Havoc! and let slip the Dogs of War!<br>Segfreid Starblaze<br>52 druid<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124467 target=akztarg><br>Azarroth Stonesinger</a><br>65 Archon</td></tr>
